# Reflection

Challenges faced in balancing stakeholder needs

The user wants a seemless interaction and ease of access to information, while the system needs to support the data processing and the infrastructure.
Solution: Opt-in option for exclusive deals while using a structured development approach (Minimum Viable Product) for development.

Integrating data from multiple sources along with the implementation of strong security measures can hamper scalibility and consistency while reducing the useability.
Solution: Use APIs and supplementing with other methods where necessary, coupled with optimal login for enhanced features.

The system would want to grow the number of users and data without degradation.
Solution: Effecient database indexing and caching mechanisms.

Compliance with variouse data sharing policies from retailers and data protection laws.
Solution: adherence to legal frameworks and offer retailers data-sharing agreements.
